# Design Narrative
# Mechanic: Deathtouch — any combat damage from a deathtouch creature destroys
#   the damaged creature, regardless of toughness.
# Forcing: Juggernaut (5/3, must attack) threatens lethal to human at 3 life.
#   Only path to survival is blocking with Typhoid Rats (1/1 deathtouch).
#   Deathtouch makes 1 damage lethal to Juggernaut despite 3 toughness.
#   No spells, no alternative plays — block or die.
# AI behavior: Juggernaut has "must attack" rules text — zero AI choice.
#   No AI hand cards, no other AI creatures. Fully deterministic.
# Failure modes:
#   WIN   = deathtouch worked, Juggernaut died, human survived
#   LOSE (human died) = deathtouch didn't fire, 5 damage got through unblocked
#   LOSE (turn limit) = impossible — Juggernaut must attack
#   TIMEOUT = combat phase wiring broken (DeclareBlockersReq not sent)
# Card roles:
#   Typhoid Rats — 1/1 deathtouch blocker, the test subject
#   Juggernaut — 5/3 must-attack creature, forces the combat interaction
# Protocol path: DeclareAttackersReq, DeclareBlockersReq, combat damage SBA.
#   All combat paths are wired.

[metadata]
Name:Deathtouch Kills Giant
Goal:Survive
Turns:2
Difficulty:Easy
Description:Block Juggernaut with Typhoid Rats. Deathtouch kills it despite 3 toughness. Survive or die.

[state]
